maybe try to build based on this commit: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/commit/7bf937274095643941919736df612aaecc08de5a

my node has not had any issues over a week on that.

 Changed to v2.33/34 and had the issue within an hour, resetting to the commit seemed to fix the issue.

Just a guess ;)

i'm also running this script since a few weeks which should scan the last log line for 'No blocks' and restarts the client. ( There are definately better ways to do this, last time a touched perl was during uni, but seems to work well enough)

```
#!/usr/bin/perl

open(my $fd, "<", "/var/log/supervisor/erigon.err.log") or die "Can't open log";
$at_end = 0;
$at_end_recurring = 0;

while(1) {
    if(eof $fd) {
        sleep 1;
        $fd->clearerr;
        $at_end_recurring += 1;
        if(at_end_recurring == 10){
          system('echo $(date -u) no new logs opening');
          open(my $fd, "<", "/var/log/supervisor/erigon.err.log") or die "Can't open log";
          $at_end_recurring = 0;
        }
        if($at_end == 0){
          system('echo $(date -u) on last log line');
          $at_end = 1;
        } 
        
        next;
    }
    my $line = <$fd>;
    chomp($line);
    $at_end_recurring = 0;
    if($at_end == 0){
      next;
    }
    if($line =~ /No block headers/) {
        system('echo $(date -u) erigon stuck - restarting');
        system("supervisorctl restart erigon");
        
    }
}
```
